author: Chris Wright
title: 'Wenger Out' banner spotted at New Zealand vs. Fiji match in Wellington
text:
about an hour ago 'Wenger Out' banner spotted at New Zealand vs. Fiji match in Wellington 
On Tuesday, New Zealand squared off against Fiji in their ongoing quest to qualify for the 2018 World Cup. 
The match took place in Wellington and while the crowd wasn't exactly thronging, it turns out that there was still a disgruntled Arsenal fan in attendance. 
Indeed, spotted draped over the perimeter wall behind the goal, hung a forlorn anti-Arsene Wenger banner. #Internationalbreak day 6 kicks off aith NZ v Fiji. #Wengerout banner included... and ppl say international football isn't relevant... pic.twitter.com/WzOz24gJgc 
Well what do you know? They really do get everywhere. 
The banner was also captured in close-up by a photographer at the Westpac Stadium. At New Zealand v Fiji world cup qualifier pic.twitter.com/UvSC2jdAzr - Cameron McIntosh (@NZPhotomac) March 28, 2017 
Given that the Westpac Stadium is roughly 11,500 miles across the other side of the world from the Emirates, you've simply got to commend the commitment to the 'Wenger Out' cause. 
Chris covers the funny side of the game for ESPN FC in the Toe Poke blog.
